Minister Nhlanhla Nene said that pursuing a fiscal policy that will stabilise the country's debt to GDP is part of government's intention. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa is committed to a prudent fiscal policy aimed at stabilising its debt to GDP ratio, Finance Minister Nhlanhla Nene said on Thursday. “Cabinet has agreed that fiscal sustainability must remain the focus,” Nene told a Moody’s conference by video link. “It is government’s intention to pursue a prudent fiscal policy that stabilises our debt to GDP ratio in the long term.” WATCH: Nhlanhla Nene addresses Moody's Sub-Saharan Africa Conference 